   ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS & EQUIPMENT (ELQ), TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS) </IN>
<TXT>
<p>
   METRICOM Inc. (Los Gatos, Calif.) -- Former Defense Secretary
Donald Rumsfeld and three business executives were named directors,
expanding the size of the board to nine from five. Mr. Rumsfeld, 61
years old, served as White House chief of staff in the Nixon
administration and as defense secretary under President Ford. The
other new members are Robert S. Cline, 56, chairman and chief
executive of the Airborne Express unit of Airborne Freight Corp.,
Seattle; Mike Slade, 36, president and chief executive of closely
held Starwave Corp., a Bellevue, Wash., supplier of multimedia
software; and Robert M. Smelick, 51, managing principal and director
of closely held Sterling Payot Co., an investment banking firm based
in San Francisco. Metricom is a supplier of wireless data
communication networks.
