<IN> SEMICONDUCTORS (SEM) </IN>
<DATELINE> SANTA CLARA, Calif. </DATELINE>
<TXT>
<p>
   Solitec Inc., blaming a shortage of cash,
said it dismissed dozens of employees at its head office and its
Compumart subsidiary in Portland, Ore.
</p>
<p>
   The company, which makes chip production equipment and
distributes electronics goods, also said that Joe McDowell, its
chief executive officer, cut his salary to the federal minimum
hourly wage and that Partha Sarathy, the chief financial officer,
had resigned.
</p>
