<HL>    Who's News:
@  El Paso Electric Co. </HL>
<DD> 01/06/94 </DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION </SO>
<CO>    ELPAQ </CO>
<IN> ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC), SOUTHERN U.S. ELECTRIC UTILITIES (UES) </IN>
<TXT>
<p>
   EL PASO ELECTRIC Co. (El Paso, Texas) -- Three senior officers
took voluntary early retirement from this utility company. They are:
William J. Johnson, 52 years old, a senior vice president and chief
financial officer; Ignacio R. Troncoso, 47, senior vice president,
operations; and William W. Royer, 49, senior vice president, special
projects. A company spokesman said the retirements were part of the
company's effort to align its corporate structure more closely with
that of Central & Southwest Corp. of Dallas, which has agreed to
acquire the company.
</p>
</TXT>
